<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-9CCAD3A9-F3AF-475D-808D-6031FC44EE61" version="2" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-9CCAD3A9-F3AF-475D-808D-6031FC44EE61" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Upgrade workflows for ORS updates</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-048A981C-B8DB-46CA-A419-6E2BE396798F"><p class="- topic/p ">Here we describe the preferred procedure to update the machines in the field with the latest firmware and latest applicable windows updates (=security updates). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">he goal is to update the MIF with the latest version to profit from the new functionalities for the customer and improvements for service with as less as effort and disturbances as possible. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Tools</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-B62E659F-C470-47ED-B66F-AB8209A2A524" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Firmware and/or windows updates</title><p class="- topic/p ">Firmware upgrades are taken to describe the process. The windows updates act slightly differently, this is especially noted when applicable. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-A332CC51-CDAC-45AE-935C-2E66FC301256" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Outline of the release process to connected machines</title><fig id="GUID-E79213B5-1153-4B33-8032-63B1E9E40C1F" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-580CA549-F994-4F99-B0C7-84DA3EB0C969-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-580CA549-F994-4F99-B0C7-84DA3EB0C969-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Settings need to be made per serial number. In the release process, 2 configuration locations are applicable. The first location is in the ORS portal (<xref href="https://prismaservice.cpp.canon" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot gentext?>https://prismaservice.cpp.canon</xref>) the second location is on the engine. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-73F2DF89-311A-450E-B171-2AD311F8D244" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Preferred workflow when a new update is received</title><p class="- topic/p ">At the release of a new upgrade, the technician needs to contact the customer about the upgrade of his engine(s). The technician plans the moment of installation with the customer. At the agreed moment the technician publishes the firmware and the software will be installed. A planned visit can also be a moment to plan a software update. Important to know is that the windows updates (= security) will bypass the manual publication and will be published to engines within 1 day of release. 
</p><note id="GUID-4F12FF44-107A-4144-B0EF-6B6121B43976" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> For the agreed moment, the download duration needs to be taken into account. 
</p></note><fig id="GUID-F3370AE2-9134-4622-BF0C-7D647887B4B6" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-2147357B-0667-4758-9C23-48327529729B-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2147357B-0667-4758-9C23-48327529729B-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-7AEF45F6-A58C-4ABF-97D9-837EE1647713" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The preferred workflow explained</title><p class="- topic/p ">At the release of a new upgrade, the technician needs to contact the customer about the upgrade of his engine(s). To check which customers need to be contacted, the service portal (<xref href="https://prismaservice.cpp.canon" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot gentext?>https://prismaservice.cpp.canon</xref>) can be used. Search via your preferred method and filter on release numbers, e.g. 
</p><fig id="GUID-79B59FF3-F838-46A5-9F11-D786E8D20FCF" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-5EF26EFD-3BCC-4F39-BA04-F89E4B4B1E00-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5EF26EFD-3BCC-4F39-BA04-F89E4B4B1E00-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">In case this is the first time this workflow is executed for an engine, the workflow needs to be explained to the customer and some settings on the engine need to be checked and if necessary changed. 
</p><sl class="- topic/sl "><sli class="- topic/sli ">Preferred setup for the customer engine settings are as follows: Enabled the download of PRISMAsync updates (= firmware update), enable the download of windows updates, set the download time to “specified time” at midnight, and set the installation time to “specified time” at midnight. Rationale: When there is an upgrade available and the technician plans with the customer a fitting moment, the customer is not bothered by additional actions. The download will start at midnight after the update is published by the technician and this will have the least impact on the normal network load. When the download is fully completed, the installation will start on the first following midnight, reducing the impact on normal operation. Additionally, the customer can be informed when an update is downloaded and installed when the option “Send email to the system administrator about the status of updates” is enabled. 
</sli></sl><p class="- topic/p ">The exact combination of settings needs to be discussed with the customer; the goal is to let the customer decide when to install and also unburden the customer at the moment of installation. Further on in the chapter the different options for configuration a described in more detail. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">On agreement of the upgrade moment, the technician will publish the update in the service portal (<xref href="https://prismaservice.cpp.canon" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot gentext?>https://prismaservice.cpp.canon</xref>) at the correct moment. In the case of the preferred setup, the download will start at the first midnight and the installation at the second midnight. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Publication in the service portal is done by opening the product by selecting the serial number, going to the “Software version” sub-menu, and clicking the publish button. 
</p><fig id="GUID-36A707D1-9A72-434D-B47C-517889232D3F" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-7143ADA4-7D38-4E5E-9BA4-9CA23C223ED2-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7143ADA4-7D38-4E5E-9BA4-9CA23C223ED2-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-4648125A-C01F-4D23-AF73-230B75680B30" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Configurable options in the ORS workflow.</title><table id="GUID-F632636C-6E39-47A5-BB87-90C730EE8958" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="4" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" namest="col1" nameend="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Configurations in the ORS Serviceportal (<xref href="https://prismaservice.cpp.canon" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot gentext?>https://prismaservice.cpp.canon</xref>) 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Firmware publishing 
</p><fig id="GUID-A85D5E75-1D88-4889-A0CD-C9C69B912FA8" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-9D38EDC6-9474-47F8-9913-991AA13B1E89-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9D38EDC6-9474-47F8-9913-991AA13B1E89-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Follow central update policy</b>. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When published by HQ the update will be published to the engine on the next ORS reconnect( daily around midnight) 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Keep current.</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">No publication to engine 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Manual publishing 
</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When HQ publishes the update this is reported here and not published to the engine until the publish button is pushed. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Windows update/Security publishing 
</p><fig id="GUID-51445936-D92B-465F-AB2B-AC055F24D3DF" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-7077D338-3617-42CB-9EA2-98696A92C9F1-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7077D338-3617-42CB-9EA2-98696A92C9F1-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">When the windows updates are published by HQ the update will be published to the engine on the next ORS reconnect( daily around midnight). The windows update publishing can be forced. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Revoke the published software to the engine. 
</p><fig id="GUID-9669F78B-DD50-4861-9C17-767872EBBFB3" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-FACBCBA2-9F12-4C65-AA82-2F42FDE4FE05-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FACBCBA2-9F12-4C65-AA82-2F42FDE4FE05-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">As long as the updates are not installed at the engine the updates offered to the engine can be revoked. The publishing settings for firmware and Windows updates as described above still apply. E.g. Not applied security updates will be published again to the engine on a reconnect. 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><table id="GUID-B16096AC-690D-46C9-AB7D-080B66D5910E" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" namest="col1" nameend="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Configurations in the Settings editor of the engine (1/3) 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Checkbox: 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Send email to system administrator about status of updates</b> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Inform the administrator by email when an update is received and is installed 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Checked 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">See the user guide on how to configure email updates. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Do not inform anyone by email 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Not checked 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table><table id="GUID-F3F714FF-4B8B-4504-B6D4-73C9CB5E5C12" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="4" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" namest="col1" nameend="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Configurations in the Settings editor of the engine (2/3) 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Receive updates to PRISMAsync checkbox 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Receive updates to the operating system checkbox 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Firmware and windows updates are accepted 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Checked 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Checked 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Preferred 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Firmware is not accepted, windows updates are accepted. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Not checked 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Checked 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Firmware updates are accepted, windows updates are not accepted. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Checked 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Not checked 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Firmware and windows updates are not accepted 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Not checked 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Not checked 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table><table id="GUID-780F35EE-727F-4ADD-9071-A3B314B7AF0B" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="5" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col5" colnum="5" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" namest="col1" nameend="col5" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Configuration in the Settings editor of the engine (3/3) 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Download moment 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Installation moment 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col5" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Remarks 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Immediate installation, moment unknown 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">immediate 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">immediate 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">When the update is downloaded completely the installation will start at the moment the printer is in standby. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The start of the download is unknown and the start of the installation depends on the download duration. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Planned installation 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">immediate 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">At specified time 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">When the update is downloaded completely the installation will start at the specified time when the printer is in standby. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">When the specified time has passed during the download the installation will start the next day at the specified time. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Manual actions of customer required 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">immediate 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Manual 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The update will be downloaded and will not be installed. The installation needs to be done manually by the customer. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The customer actions are described in the user guide. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See: 
<xref keyref="ExtOperationGuide" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-250A5CF0-B4FF-4B2C-B7C2-66A319226098.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="reference"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>Operation and Safety information</xref> and available videos. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Immediate installation, moment unknown 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">At specified time 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">immediate 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The download will be done at the specified time. When completed the installation will start at the moment the printer is in standby. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The installation moment depends on the download speed of the customer. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Planned installation 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">At specified time 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">At specified time 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The download will be done at the specified time. The installation will start at the specified time when the printer is in standby. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">When the specified time has passed during the download the installation will start the next day at the specified time. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Manual actions of customer required 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">At specified time 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Manual 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The download will be done at the specified time. The installation needs to be started manually by the customer 
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The customer actions are described in the user guide. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See: 
